text: Sajid Javid said that Covid-19 deaths in the UK had been overestimated.
Around 17,000 people have died of Covid-19 in Britain.
Far more people have died of Covid-19 in the UK than in Japan
From 21 July to 25 July the UK reported 426 Covid-19 deaths.
18 people died of Covid-19 in one day in England.
No more than 100,000 people have died of Covid in the UK.
